# 7. TCP Connect Scan

## Objective

Compare SYN scan with a full TCP connection scan.

## Command

```bash
nmap -sT <TARGET-IP>
```

## Output File

```bash
nmap -sT <TARGET-IP> -oN raw-output/tcp-connect-scan.txt
```

## Explanation

- `-sT` completes the TCP three-way handshake.
- Easier to detect.
- Works without root privileges.

